did.unittitle: Indiana University School of Journalism Chair's records

origination.label: Creator
origination.corpname: Indiana University, Bloomington. School of Journalism.

did.abstract: The School of Journalism at Indiana University was established within the College of Arts and Sciences in 1911 as the Department of Journalism. The name was changed in 1974 to the School of Journalism, and it became an independent school in the IU system in 1986. This collection consists of records collected by the Office of the Chair primarily during the tenure of John E. Stempel, who was chairman from 1938-1968.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: Collection is open for research. Advance notice required.

bioghist.head: Administrative History
bioghist.p: The School of Journalism was established in 1911 as the Department of Journalism and was at that time part of the College of Arts and Sciences. In 1932, IU students could earn a bachelor's degree in journalism for the first time. The name of the department was changed in 1974 to the School of Journalism, but remained as part of the College of Arts and Sciences. In 1982, it became a system-wide school, coordinating journalism courses across all eight campuses. It became an independent school within the IU system in 1986.

John E. Stempel was head of the Department of Journalism from 1938 until he retired in 1968. He was a classmate of famed World War II reporter Ernie Pyle at Indiana University. During Stempel's chairmanship, the School of Journalism moved to Ernie Pyle Hall, where it remains today. In addition, it was during his leadership that the highly-respected High School Journalism Institute was established in the summer of 1946.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is organized into one series, Administrative files, and arranged in alphabetical order.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Note
scopecontent.p: The collection has been organized into a single series of Administrative files, arranged alphabetically by folder heading. The records span 1922-1976, with the bulk dating from 1938-1968. Materials in the collection include correspondence, staff records, research, clippings, reports, contests, and information on organizations and departments. Prominent in the collection are faculty annual reports, records related to the Associated Press and its state photo contest headed by John E. Stempel, workshops developed and run by the school, departmental correspondence, and records related to the Indiana Daily Student and other campus publications.

separatedmaterial.head: Separated Material
separatedmaterial.p: IU newspaper and magazine publications that were not related to research or correspondence were pulled.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Material
relatedmaterial.p: Additional records such as newsletters, annual reports, bulletins, and publications may be accessed in the Archives of Institutional Memory
Archived web sites for the School may be included in Archive-It
Related photographs may be available in the University Archives Photographs Database

userestrict.p: Copyrights for records originating with Indiana University administrative units, departments, and other offices are held by the Trustees of Indiana University. For more information, please contact the Indiana University Archives staff.

The Indiana University Archives respects the intellectual property rights of others and does not claim any copyrights for non-university records, materials in the public domain, or materials for which we do not hold a Deed of Gift. Responsibility for the determination of the copyright status of these materials rests with those persons wishing to reuse the materials. Researchers are responsible for securing permission from copyright owners and any other rights holders for any reuse of these materials that extends beyond fair use or other statutory limitations.

Digital reproductions of archival materials from the Indiana University Archives are made available for noncommercial educational and research purposes only. If you are the copyright holder for any of the digitized materials and have questions about its inclusion on our site, please contact the Indiana University Archivist.

prefercite.p: [Item], Indiana University School of Journalism Chair's records, Collection C467, Indiana University Archives, Bloomington.

custodhist.head: Provenance
custodhist.p: Transferred from the School of Journalism to the University Archives, 22 August 2003.

appraisal.head: Appraisal
appraisal.p: Duplicate materials were removed and discarded. Documents containing social security numbers and grades were removed and shredded. Empty folders were removed.
